      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVOLVE (5) stalked the lead from a low draw and fought on well to finish 3 lengths back in third (19.85) at this track in a Grade 6 over 342m. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Makes plenty of appeal. MAFIA MISTRESS (7) had been racing well prior to her last start fourth at this track following a TG1-4W win three back with a third placing. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Well placed here and can atone this time. MASTER KILCOY (8) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at this track in a handy 20.07 beating KILCOY LASS. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. ROYALE MAPLE (1) is another with top-three prospects.",
